# --- Ranch OS Gate Development Overlay ---
#
# Merged on top of gate.fragment + dev.fragment when the build runs with
# RANCH_BUILD_PROFILE=development AND the target is the gate. Adds an
# SSH-over-USB-ethernet path so a developer can `ssh root@<dhcp-ip>` into
# a gate without HDMI (Pi Zero W has only mini-HDMI, easy to be without
# the right cable in the field).
#
# Why this is gate-only and not in the shared dev.fragment:
#   - The base station already runs NetworkManager, which manages every
#     interface it sees. Running systemd-networkd alongside NM with a
#     wildcard .network file on the same box would race for control of
#     wlan0 / eth0 on the Pi 3. The base never needs USB-eth dev access
#     anyway — it's reachable over the operator's home Wi-Fi by design.
#   - The gate fragment turns off networkd entirely (LoRa-only,
#     deliberately no IP stack in prod). We re-enable it here, but only
#     when the dev profile is in play.

# Re-enable systemd-networkd to manage hotplugged ethernet interfaces.
# Overrides BR2_PACKAGE_SYSTEMD_NETWORKD=n in gate.fragment via the standard
# merge_config.sh "later wins" rule. Vendor preset enables the unit at
# preset-all time, so we don't need a manual wants-symlink — Buildroot's
# `systemctl preset-all` step (run by SYSTEMD_INSTALL_INIT_PRESET in
# SYSTEMD_TARGET_FINALIZE_HOOKS) wipes manually-installed
# target.wants/ symlinks pointing at /usr/lib units anyway.
BR2_PACKAGE_SYSTEMD_NETWORKD=y

# Append a gate-dev-only rootfs overlay alongside the shared one. Buildroot
# accepts a space-separated list and applies overlays in order; files in
# later overlays win on conflict. The redefinition warning from
# merge_config.sh on this line is expected.
BR2_ROOTFS_OVERLAY="$(BR2_EXTERNAL_RANCH_OS_PATH)/rootfs-overlay $(BR2_EXTERNAL_RANCH_OS_PATH)/rootfs-overlay-gate-dev"
